HB 998/25 – W&M
By: Calvert County Delegation
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
Committee Report: Favorable
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 7, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Calvert County – Property Tax Credit – Tobacco Barns
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing the governing body of Calvert County to grant a property
4 tax credit against the county property tax imposed on certain real property that was
5 formerly used solely as a tobacco barn; and generally relating to a property tax credit
6 in Calvert County for real property that was formerly used as a tobacco barn.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Tax – Property
9 Section 9–306(i)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Tax – Property
15 9–306.
16 (I) (1) THE GOVERNING BODY OF CALVERT COUNTY MAY GRANT, BY
17 LAW, A PROPERTY TAX CREDIT AGAINST THE COUNTY PROPERTY TAX IMPOSED ON
18 REAL PROPERTY THAT WAS FORMERLY USED SOLELY AS A TOBACCO BARN IF THE
19 REAL PROPERTY:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb1095*

2 HOUSE BILL 1095
1 (I) IS LOCATED ON LAND THAT IS SUBJECT TO A TOBACCO
2 BUYOUT AGREEMENT; OR
3 (II) 1. IS LOCATED ON LAND THAT QUALIFIES FOR AN
4 AGRICULTURAL USE ASSESSMENT; AND
5 2. IS USED IN CONNECTION WITH AN ACTIVITY THAT IS
6 RECOGNIZED BY THE DEPARTMENT AS AN APPROVED AGRICULTURAL ACTIVITY.
7 (2) IN AUTHORIZING A CREDIT UNDER THIS SUBSECTION, THE
8 GOVERNING BODY OF THE COUNTY MAY PROVIDE, BY LAW, FOR:
9 (I) THE AMOUNT OF THE CREDIT;
10 (II) THE DURATION OF THE CREDIT; AND
11 (III) ANY OTHER PROVISION NECESSARY TO ADMINISTER THE
12 CREDIT.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
14 1, 2026, and shall be applicable to all taxable years beginning after June 30, 2026.
Approved:
